A Free Public Wi-Fi (FPWI) is a mini-network that allows people to access the internet and contributes financial benefit to the local economy, particularly to the people around the area.

FPWI is a network that provides internet connection through unlicensed spectrums and it is specifically designed for publicly accessible areas such as coffee shops, libraries, community centers, universities, government centers, and travel hubs. While the Free Public Wi-Fi is often established to provide access to users, to a greater degree, and FPWI also creates financial benefits for the cities and towns in which it is created.

Together, these technologies innovate in order to provide a combination of privacy and anonymity.
